<subsection xml:id="Problem_OE3_10">
    <title>Problem 9_2_5</title>
    <p>
        If <m>n=1</m>, <m>p=7</m> so <m>2</m> is a quadratic residue and hence not a primitve root.
    </p>
      <p>
        If <m>n=2</m>, <m>p=13</m> and the table in chapter 8 shows that <m>2</m> is a primitive root.
      </p>  
      <p>
        If <m>n &gt; 2</m>, <m>p \equiv 1 \pmod{8}</m> so <m>2</m> is a quadratic residue and hence not a primitve root.
    </p>
</subsection>

